        <p class="teaser">
            Bee Gees brothers Barry, Maurice and Robin Gibb were one of the world&#39;s popular groups of all time, thanks to their mix of pop, folk and disco classics from the 1960s to the 2000s. Their &#39;Saturday Night Fever&#39; soundtrack is one of the best-selling film albums ever, and the Gibb brothers wrote and produced for many other top artists.
        </p>
    
    
        <p class="expanded">
            Members: Barry Gibb, Maurice Gibb, Robin Gibb<br />Years active: 1958-2003<br />Records sold: 220 million<br />Albums: 22<br />Singles: 83<br />Best songs:<br />- Massachusetts <br />- Words<br />- I Started a Joke<br />- How Can You Mend a Broken Heart?<br />- Jive Talkin&#39;<br />- Nights on Broadway<br />- You Should Be Dancing<br />- How Deep is Your Love<br />- More than a Woman<br />- Stayin&#39; Alive<br />- Night Fever<br />- Tragedy<br />- Love You Inside Out<br />- You Win Again<br />- Alone<br />- This Is Where I Came In
        </p>
        <a href="#" class="toggle is-hidden" data-action="toggle"
           >
            View more
        </a>
    
</div>

        
            
